profile:
Tom Zhang Structural Engineers ----647-706-2668
Structural engineers (P.Eng.) with more than 30 years’ experience in wood, masonry, concrete and steel design for residential, industrial and commercial buildings. Licensed and fully insured. We provide structural engineering services to property owners, general contractors, and architects. Professional services include: 

-Engineer letter & Report for City Building Inspector

-General Review Letter for the City

Inspection Report for Bank

Inspection Report for Insurance

-Load-bearing wall removal

Structural Assessments of existing building

Design of LVL beams

Connection Design

Foundation Design for Industrial buildings

Load Bearing Wall and column removal for open space concept

Addition and alteration to existing building

 Signage Design

Structural Building  Permit Drawing Review & Stamping


- Structural Steel & miscellaneous Steel Shop Drawing Review and Stamping

Site Inspection & Certification Letter

-Permit Drawings, as built Drawings 

--Earth Retaining Structural Design

-Roof top unit supporting System

-Solar Panel Supporting System Design & Review

-Walkout Basement

Curtain Wall & Glass Shop Drawing Review & Stamping

-Curtain-wall Design, Shop drawing preparation.

-Structural Glass Systems Design, Drawing Stamping.

- Foundation and Wall Designs

Drafting with AutoCAD

 
Service Areas:

St Catharines, Niagara Falls, Welland, Thorold, Niagara Region, Toronto, Etobicoke, North York, Scarborough, York Region (Richmond Hill, Vaughan, Aurora, Newmarket), Bradford, Markham and Mississauga. Peel, Milton, Brampton, Hamilton.

Alberta, B.C., Saskatchewan, Newfoundland, Northwest Territories.
 
Our services are conducted/supervised by licensed professional engineers and licensed architects. Our rates are extremely reasonable. We offer high quality work with a quick and efficient turnaround time.  we are flexible to your schedule.
